I truly love this place. I am a law student a few blocks North and truly miss late 11pm study sessions with friends and McDonald’s afties. Or bachelor nights with McChickens. While I do wish it was open later, it is probably better for my health it is not. My go to is a McChicken because I try not to eat too much red meat. The Diet Coke here? Second to none. I never know how they do it—but it’s flame. The fries? Unbeatable. The Sprite? Sublime. Truly an all around incredible experience.  Today, I tried the spicy nuggets to go. I was nervous because I saw a line out the door when I was walking by a little before, but I should have known the McClurg McDonald’s would come through. I ordered in the app, entered the store, and they promptly served the nuggets. As an aside, they have excellent COVID protocols and barriers. “Thank you!” Says the masked worked cheerily. “No, thank you!” I say back. I had no idea I was prepared for the most exquisite culinary experience of my short little lifetime. I take my pickup order home, try a nugget, and was transported to a world that was not my own. I got a side of ranch sauce, dipped, and again—magic. I did not know my love for the McClurg McDonald’s could grow larger than before, but again, they have surpassed all expectations.
